    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-wholewheat-spaghetti-carbonara/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-wholewheat-spaghetti-carbonara/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pastais cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> meat-free bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until golden and crispy all over</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-wholewheat-spaghetti-carbonara/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>crispy meat-free bacon</strong> to a bowl and return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>diced shallot </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once starting to soften, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-wholewheat-spaghetti-carbonara/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine <strong>half</strong> of your<strong> cider vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>in a bowl and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-wholewheat-spaghetti-carbonara/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic is fragrant, reduce the heat to medium-low and add your<strong> creamy single soy</strong>, <strong>miso </strong>and<strong> remaining cider vinegar</strong></p><p>Tip: The miso paste adds an umami flavour to the sauce!</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened to a creamy consistency</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-wholewheat-spaghetti-carbonara/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the<strong> cooked pasta </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the pasta is fully coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>plant-based pasta carbonara</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if the sauce is a little thick!</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-wholewheat-spaghetti-carbonara/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>plant-based pasta carbonara </strong>and top with the<strong> crispy meat-free bacon</strong> and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Toss the <strong>salad </strong>and <strong>diced tomato</strong>, then serve to the side and drizzle over the <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
